content:
A calculation procedure is a series of calculations performed on matrix lookups, user-defined variables, and constants. A calculation matrix is a table that looks up information using multiple input dimensions and returns the corresponding output value.

Calculation procedures and matrices can automate complex quotes by guiding users through questions, pulling data from sources, and presenting customized quotes or eligibility determinations.

Examples of use include:

* Individual health insurance plans
* Term life quotes
* Volume discounts
* Permits or application fees
* Benefits or services applications

Inputs come from Salesforce forms, REST APIs, OmniScripts, or Integration Procedures. Outputs can be proposals or PDFs, data for populating scripts, forms, lists, JSON structures, or REST API requests.

A calculation procedure involves:

* Matrix lookups to find corresponding outputs
* Use of user-defined variables and constants
* Ability to call Apex classes for custom logic
* Part of pricing rules

Declarative calculation procedures are key components of ratings engines, along with calculation matrices. They take input JSON and run through matrix lookups and calculations to calculate ratings for policy products.
title: Vlocity Calculation Procedures and Matrices
